One of the most important things when racing and training, specially long races, or being out for a long mountain trip is hydration.
Keep hydrated is not only important to perform better but also to recover faster and to keep the organs and tissues healthy and prevent injuries.
Deshydration causes fatigue, decreases performance, and an increase the body temperature, heart rate, and perceived exertion. This is when we have loss more than 2 percent of body weight.

To keep well hydrated during a run can seem easy but it isn't. Normally we should listen to our thirst, but because when we run in the mountains we can not stop wherever we want to find water and if we need to carry-it it can be a lot of weight. So we should make a strategy on where we can refill, how much until next point, how and where to carry (or to melt, find water) Or during long runs when exhaustion is hight, we can easly forgot to drink or to eat, even if we are thirsty or hungry or those feelings can go away due to the fatigue.
So, normally depending external temperature and our temperature acclimatazion we should drink between 0,4 and 1 liter every hour. The best is to drink a bit every 15 minutes. Small, frequent sips are ideal. A tip to see that we are well hydared is when is easy to spit. That is easy to do in a race or short runs when we can find water every few hours and carry all what we need, but more difficult in some unassisted trips or mountaineering when we need to find ok compromises.
For the everyday or before a race it is important to keep well hydrated and for that the easiest way to check is with the color of the urine, and keep drinking until is clear.
Another long term approach to get the body working as efficient as possible is to do some long runs/days without water and food, but that should be a long term (years) strategy and need to be done in small amounts and progressive to avoid big problems.
When I train I only drink flat water and in races normally I carry or drink from aidstations flat water and another with water with some carbs or with salt if it is hot. And longer it is more flat water to keep good stomach.
What are your hydration tips?
